  "blurb": "A two-villa estate on Bali's scenic south-west coast at Seseh Beach, with panoramic views over the rice fields to the Indian Ocean — eleven bedrooms across a seven-bedroom villa and a four-bedroom companion, two pools, a pitch-and-putt green, a sauna and open-air massage pavilions, ten minutes from Canggu and set up to host up to twenty-two guests.",
  "detail": "Set on the scenic south-west coast at Seseh Beach, this estate brings together two villas — a seven-bedroom main house and a four-bedroom companion — for a combined eleven bedrooms that sleep up to twenty-two. Panoramic views run over luxuriant rice fields all the way to the Indian Ocean, and the layout of pavilions and gardens keeps large groups comfortably spread out.\n\nThe grounds are generous: two swimming pools, a pitch-and-putt golf green, a sauna, open-air massage pavilions and multiple dining areas set among tropical gardens. Between the two villas there is room for everyone to gather or find their own corner, which makes the estate a natural fit for multi-generation holidays, retreats and weddings.\n\nA full team of staff — private chefs, butlers and attendants — looks after both villas throughout the stay. Canggu is about ten minutes away, with the sea temple of Tanah Lot close by along the coast, while the estate itself stays quiet behind its rice-field frontage.",
